      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-03-29T21:09:07Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDate>2017-10-05</actionDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Opioid Addiction Prevention Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Controlled Substances Act to prohibit the Drug Enforcement Administration from registering, or renewing the registration of, a practitioner who is licensed to prescribe opioids in schedule II, III, or IV unless the practitioner agrees to comply with certain requirements when prescribing opioids for the initial treatment of acute pain, such as a limit on the initial supply.</p> <p>An opioid that is approved and prescribed for the treatment of addiction is not subject to the requirements. </p>]]></text>
